CancelAllMatchmakingTicketsForPlayerRequ.name: CancelAllMatchmakingTicketsForPlayerRequest
CancelAllMatchmakingTicketsForPlayerRequ.description: Cancels all tickets of which the player is a member in a given queue that are not cancelled or matched. This API is useful if you lose track of what tickets the player is a member of (if the title crashes for instance) and want to "reset". The Entity field is optional if the caller is a player and defaults to that player. Players may not cancel tickets for other people. The Entity field is required if the caller is a server (authenticated as the title).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity key of the player whose tickets should be canceled.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The name of the queue from which a player's tickets should be canceled.

CancelAllServerBackfillTicketsForPlayerR.name: CancelAllServerBackfillTicketsForPlayerRequest
CancelAllServerBackfillTicketsForPlayerR.description: Cancels all backfill tickets of which the player is a member in a given queue that are not cancelled or matched. This API is useful if you lose track of what tickets the player is a member of (if the server crashes for instance) and want to "reset".

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity key of the player whose backfill tickets should be canceled.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The name of the queue from which a player's backfill tickets should be canceled.

CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest.name: CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest
CancelMatchmakingTicketRequest.description: Only servers and ticket members can cancel a ticket. The ticket can be in five different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is waiting for members to join it, and it has not started matching. If the ticket is cancelled at this stage, it will never match. 2: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 3: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 4: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. 5: the ticket is waiting for a server. If the ticket is cancelled, server allocation will be stopped. A server may still be allocated due to a race condition, but that will not be reflected in the ticket. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the client making a cancellation request. The client must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because players must consent to enter matchmaking again. Create a new ticket instead.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The name of the queue the ticket is in.

properties.name: TicketId
properties.description: The Id of the ticket to find a match for.

CancelServerBackfillTicketRequest.name: CancelServerBackfillTicketRequest
CancelServerBackfillTicketRequest.description: Only servers can cancel a backfill ticket. The ticket can be in three different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 2: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 3: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the server making a cancellation request. The server must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket. Create a new ticket instead.

properties.name: QueueName
properties.description: The name of the queue the ticket is in.

properties.name: TicketId
properties.description: The Id of the ticket to find a match for.

This API is useful if you lose track of what tickets the player is a member of (if the title crashes for instance) and want to "reset". The Entity field is optional if the caller is a player and defaults to that player. Players may not cancel tickets for other people. The Entity field is required if the caller is a server (authenticated as the title).

calls.name: CancelMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Cancel a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Only servers and ticket members can cancel a ticket. The ticket can be in five different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is waiting for members to join it, and it has not started matching. If the ticket is cancelled at this stage, it will never match. 2: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 3: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 4: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. 5: the ticket is waiting for a server. If the ticket is cancelled, server allocation will be stopped. A server may still be allocated due to a race condition, but that will not be reflected in the ticket. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the client making a cancellation request. The client must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket because players must consent to enter matchmaking again. Create a new ticket instead.

calls.name: CancelServerBackfillTicket
calls.summary: Cancel a server backfill ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Only servers can cancel a backfill ticket. The ticket can be in three different states when it is cancelled. 1: the ticket is matching. If the ticket is cancelled, it will stop matching. 2: the ticket is matched. A matched ticket cannot be cancelled. 3: the ticket is already cancelled and nothing happens. There may be race conditions between the ticket getting matched and the server making a cancellation request. The server must handle the possibility that the cancel request fails if a match is found before the cancellation request is processed. We do not allow resubmitting a cancelled ticket. Create a new ticket instead.

calls.name: CreateRemoteUser

calls.requestDetails: The server specifies all the members, their teams and their attributes, and the server details if applicable.

calls.name: CreateServerMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Create a matchmaking ticket as a server. The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against other matchmaking tickets.
calls.requestDetails: The server specifies all the members and their attributes.

calls.name: EnableMultiplayerServersForTitle
calls.summary: Enables the multiplayer server feature for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Enables the multiplayer server feature for a title and returns the enabled status. The enabled status can be Initializing, Enabled, and Disabled. It can up to 20 minutes or more for the title to be enabled for the feature. On average, it can take up to 20 minutes for the title to be enabled for the feature.

calls.name: EnablePartiesForTitle
calls.summary: Enables the parties feature for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Enables the parties feature for a title.

calls.name: GetAssetUploadUrl
calls.summary: Gets the URL to upload assets to.
calls.requestDetails: Gets the URL to upload assets to.

calls.name: GetBuild
calls.summary: Gets a multiplayer server build.
calls.requestDetails: Returns the details about a multiplayer server build.

calls.name: GetCognitiveServicesLocales
calls.summary: Gets supported locales for the cognitive services based on the specified service type.
calls.requestDetails: Gets supported locales for the cognitive services where translation queries can be sent to.

calls.name: GetCognitiveServicesToken
calls.summary: Gets a token for the cognitive services based on the specified service type.
calls.requestDetails: Gets a token for the cognitive services where translation queries can be sent to.

calls.name: GetContainerRegistryCredentials
calls.summary: Gets the credentials to the container registry.
calls.requestDetails: Gets credentials to the container registry where game developers can upload custom container images to before creating a new build.

calls.name: GetMatch
calls.summary: Get a match.
calls.requestDetails: When matchmaking has successfully matched together a collection of tickets, it produces a 'match' with an Id. The match contains all of the players that were matched together, and their team assigments. Only servers and ticket members can get the match.

calls.name: GetMatchmakingQueue
calls.summary: Get a matchmaking queue configuration.
calls.requestDetails: Gets the current configuration for a queue.

calls.name: GetMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Get a matchmaking ticket by ticket Id.
calls.requestDetails: The ticket includes the invited players, their attributes if they have joined, the ticket status, the match Id when applicable, etc. Only servers, the ticket creator and the invited players can get the ticket.

calls.name: GetMultiplayerServerDetails
calls.summary: Gets multiplayer server session details for a build.
calls.requestDetails: Gets multiplayer server session details for a build in a specific region.

calls.name: GetMultiplayerServerLogs
calls.summary: Gets multiplayer server logs after a server has terminated.
calls.requestDetails: Gets multiplayer server logs for a specific server id in a region. The logs are available only after a server has terminated.

calls.name: GetQueueStatistics
calls.summary: Get the statistics for a queue.
calls.requestDetails: Returns the matchmaking statistics for a queue. These include the number of players matching and the statistics related to the time to match statistics in seconds (average and percentiles). Statistics are refreshed once every 5 minutes. Servers can access all statistics no matter what the ClientStatisticsVisibility is configured to. Clients can access statistics according to the ClientStatisticsVisibility. Client requests are forbidden if all visibility fields are false.

calls.name: GetRemoteLoginEndpoint
calls.summary: Gets a remote login endpoint to a VM that is hosting a multiplayer server build.
calls.requestDetails: Gets a remote login endpoint to a VM that is hosting a multiplayer server build in a specific region.

calls.name: GetServerBackfillTicket
calls.summary: Get a matchmaking backfill ticket by ticket Id.
calls.requestDetails: The ticket includes the players, their attributes, their teams, the ticket status, the match Id and the server details when applicable, etc. Only servers can get the ticket.

calls.name: GetTitleEnabledForMultiplayerServersStatus
calls.summary: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature.
calls.requestDetails: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature. The enabled status can be Initializing, Enabled, and Disabled.

calls.name: GetTitleMultiplayerServersQuotas
calls.summary: Gets the quotas for a title in relation to multiplayer servers.
calls.requestDetails: Gets the quotas for a title in relation to multiplayer servers.

calls.name: JoinMatchmakingTicket
calls.summary: Join a matchmaking ticket.
calls.requestDetails: Add the player to a matchmaking ticket and specify all of its matchmaking attributes. Players can join a ticket if and only if their EntityKeys are already listed in the ticket's Members list. The matchmaking service automatically starts matching the ticket against other matchmaking tickets once all players have joined the ticket. It is not possible to join a ticket once it has started matching.

calls.name: ListArchivedMultiplayerServers

calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of archived multiplayer servers for a build in a specific region.

calls.name: ListAssetSummaries

calls.name: ListBuildSummaries
calls.summary: Lists summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title. Accepts tokens for title and if game client access is enabled, allows game client to request list of builds with player entity token.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title.

calls.name: ListCertificateSummaries
calls.summary: Lists multiplayer server game certificates for a title.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer server game certificates for a title.

calls.name: ListContainerImages

calls.name: ListContainerImageTags

calls.name: ListMatchmakingQueues

calls.name: ListMatchmakingTicketsForPlayer
calls.summary: List all matchmaking ticket Ids the user is a member of.
calls.requestDetails: If the caller is a title, the EntityKey in the request is required. If the caller is a player, then it is optional. If it is provided it must match the caller's entity.

calls.name: ListMultiplayerServers
calls.summary: Lists multiplayer server sessions for a build.
calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer servers for a build in a specific region.

calls.name: ListPartyQosServers

calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of quality of service servers for party.

calls.name: ListQosServers

calls.requestDetails: Returns a list of quality of service servers.

calls.name: ListQosServersForTitle
calls.summary: Lists quality of service servers.

calls.name: ListServerBackfillTicketsForPlayer

calls.name: RemoveMatchmakingQueue
calls.summary: Remove a matchmaking queue config.
calls.requestDetails: Deletes the configuration for a queue. This will permanently delete the configuration and players will no longer be able to match in the queue. All outstanding matchmaking tickets will be cancelled.

calls.summary: Request a multiplayer server session. Accepts tokens for title and if game client access is enabled, allows game client to request a server with player entity token.
calls.requestDetails: Requests a multiplayer server session from a particular build in any of the given preferred regions.

calls.name: RequestParty

calls.requestDetails: Requests a party session from a particular build in any of the given preferred regions.

calls.name: RolloverContainerRegistryCredentials
calls.summary: Rolls over the credentials to the container registry.
calls.requestDetails: Gets new credentials to the container registry where game developers can upload custom container images to before creating a new build.

calls.name: SetMatchmakingQueue
calls.summary: Create or update a matchmaking queue configuration.
calls.requestDetails: Use this API to create or update matchmaking queue configurations. The queue configuration defines the matchmaking rules. The matchmaking service will match tickets together according to the configured rules. Queue resources are not spun up by calling this API. Queues are created when the first ticket is submitted.

calls.name: ShutdownMultiplayerServer
calls.summary: Shuts down a multiplayer server session.
calls.requestDetails: Executes the shutdown callback from the GSDK and terminates the multiplayer server session. The callback in the GSDK will allow for graceful shutdown with a 15 minute timeoutIf graceful shutdown has not been completed before 15 minutes have elapsed, the multiplayer server session will be forcefully terminated on it's own.

calls.name: UpdateBuildRegions
calls.summary: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.
calls.requestDetails: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.

calls.name: UploadCertificate
calls.summary: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
calls.requestDetails: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
